CLOSE


Name 
         close - does a close on a semaphore
         
         
        
SYNOPSIS
         #include <lib.h>
         #include <unistd.h>
         int close (void)
         
         
DESCRIPTION

        CLOSE causes the calling process to close a semaphore if no process is waiting on that semaphore. If no 
        process is waiting on a semaphore then the pointer to the semaphore is released and set to NULL. CLOSE is done 
        successfully.        
        
RETURN VALUE

Upon successful close, 1 is returned. On unsuccessful close -1 is returned.

ERRORS

On reference of a pointer to NULL memory, error is generated

